<p>ANS:</p>
<p>Hi David,   </p>
<p>Welcome to the forums   </p>
<p>I haven't tested it, but try;</p>
<p>RewriteEngine on<br />
RewriteBase /<br />
RewriteCond %{HTTP_REFERER} !^<a href="http://www\\.your\_domain\_name\\.com/">http://www\\.your\_domain\_name\\.com/</a> [NC]<br />
RewriteCond %{HTTP_REFERER} !^<a href="http://www\\.OKdomain1\\.com/">http://www\\.OKdomain1\\.com/</a> [NC]<br />
RewriteCond %{HTTP_REFERER} !^<a href="http://www\\.OKdomain2\\.com/">http://www\\.OKdomain2\\.com/</a> [NC]<br />
RewriteRule ^.*$ <a href="http://www.your\_domain\_name.com/not\_allowed\_here.htm">http://www.your\_domain\_name.com/not\_allowed\_here.htm</a> [R=301,L]</p>
<p>or I'd try something along those lines anyway - with the not_allowed_here.htm being a page I redirected all those I don't want to.</p>